just_use primitives.py

# label: WORKHORSE
# role: canonical PRIMITIVE → GESTURE library (the drift-fix)

The pipeline is **VERBs → PRIMITIVEs → GESTUREs**. This module
owns the last hop. Anything that wants to send a primitive to
the server should import from here:

- `to_wire_shape(prim, board)` — index-based primitive →
  CardStack-ref wire shape.
- `apply_locally(board, prim)` — mirror of server-side board
  mutation; lets gesture synth see correct pre-primitive state
  for the next primitive in the same trick without a /state
  round-trip.
- `send_one(client, sid, prim, board, *, verbose=False)` —
  synthesize gesture metadata, translate to wire, POST,
  advance local board.
- `cards_of(stack)` / `find_stack_index(board, cards)` —
  content-based stack identification (used by the verbs
  layer).

## Why this exists

Pre-2026-04-25 these helpers were copy-pasted across
`auto_player.py`, `agent_board_lab.py`, `analyze_trick_coverage.py`,
`beginner_hunt.py`, `one_card_hunt.py`. Steve flagged the
drift and asked for libraries. `auto_player.py` now imports
here; the other duplicates remain inline and should migrate
opportunistically.

